<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Rayne:
[B] [QUOTE]Originally posted by Aunoa:
[b]I missed a point somewhere - what does this achieve?  What does this improve & for whom?  I don't see at all how switching to this method makes it fair for all.  

.....

Again, i dont see the point of switching to a raid capable group camp.  What does it achieve that a little respect for a lone camper does not?

Noa.[/b][/QUOTE]
Bless you for asking these questions.

What does [i]my opinion[/i] that people must be completely ready to deal with Ragefire as he spawn achieve?  Um, hopefully it injects some reality into the situation.  Because the next person I read complaining that their Ragefire was stolen while they were buffing is going to get re-directed to this thread.  Work out any kind of deal you want with other Clerics.  But when the moment of truth comes and some Cleric is not responding to you as his level 60 guildmates keep pouring into Nagafen's lair, well, think about it.

If you're on a server where a list is kept, or any other kind of universally accepted sharing arrangement that's wonderful.  But keep in mind that "lists" are the savior of the week, not the strong.  It's civilized and certainly takes a lot of pressure off people, but when Cleric #87 decides this bites and just takes a spawn, where's your list then?

People complain that they cannot compete with the uber-guilds.  Bzzz.  Wrong.  You can.  Ragefire is easy and doesn't take a huge crew to do him.  I told you how to compete.  Be there, ready, and prepared for the duration of your camp.  Yes, you might not see him for a night, or many nights.  That's the Ragefire camp.  But if you are ready when he does spawn and you were there first with your force uber-guild FU can kiss your butt.  That's how you compete.  

Uber-guilds are much more organized than casual guilds.  They're moving with complete knowledge of what to do while some smaller guilds are still figuring out what buffs to throw.  That's why they win.  Superior levels and equipment help, but they acquired those levels and equipment through knowledge.  So I've told you how to compete (that be ready thing).  Now stop making excuses and either compete or concede.

And that [b]is[/b] fair.

Rayne[/B][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
